subSubSection.paragraph:
Vernacular names
:—There are recorded for this species the following vernacular names (all in Portuguese): “Jacaré” (
F.S. Araújo et al. 1291
), “Quixaba” (
L.W. Lima-Verde et al. 384
) and “Guabiraba” (
A.S.F. Castro 2265
). The first one is most commonly found in collections and its translation means “caiman”, an allusion to the stiff-exfoliating greyish bark.
